From: Alexander Usyskin <alexander.usyskin@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jun 2016 14:53:12 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 2463/2508] mei: move read cb to complete queue if not
 connected

commit a5c18eef8f2b4477fd4754325f3ff3cd9fbe2496 from
https://github.com/01org/linux-apollolake-i

Move read cb to the completion queue if a read finds out that client
is not connected. This expedite user space reader wake on error
condition.

Change-Id: I036eac2f4c358bc4c68bd5f397df75f71b6df768
Signed-off-by: Alexander Usyskin <alexander.usyskin@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>
---
 drivers/misc/mei/interrupt.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/mei/interrupt.c b/drivers/misc/mei/interrupt.c
index 436ecda..412229e 100644
--- a/drivers/misc/mei/interrupt.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/mei/interrupt.c
@@ -113,6 +113,7 @@ int mei_cl_irq_read_msg(struct mei_cl *cl,
 
 	if (!mei_cl_is_connected(cl)) {
 		cl_dbg(dev, cl, "not connected\n");
+		list_move_tail(&cb->list, &complete_list->list);
 		cb->status = -ENODEV;
 		goto out;
 	}
